President Uhuru Kenyatta and Opposition leader Raila Odinga have been spotted together again after they made up a fortnight ago. The two were seen during the close of the 2018 Barclays Kenya at Muthaiga Golf Club, Nairobi on March 25. Clad in a white shirt, black trousers and a cream cap, Uhuru was seen greeting Raila with an amusement as other officials around them smiled and laughed. Raila who was also clad in a jungle green trouser, navy blue shirt and a cap marching his trouser greeted Uhuru as they walked towards the golf. "It was nice watching the 2018 Barclays Kenya Open but I think I'll stick to watching the Mighty Gor Mahia," Raila wrote on his Twitter handle.  President Uhuru Kenyatta and Opposition leader Raila Odinga at the Muthaiga gold club./PSCU The two seem to have taken their friendship a notch higher as they came together for economic stability and development in the country. ODM and Jubilee government are working together to bring Kenyans together and end electoral justice and Kenya. The two were accompanied by Nairobi governor Mike Sonko, Tourism CS Najib Balala alongside other government officials.  President Uhuru Kenyatta with former Prime Minister Raila Odinga during the 2018 Barclays Kenya Open at Muthaiga Golf Club, Nairobi../pscu Raila's ODM party has maintained that it will continue to play its role as the opposition party, but will always engage the government on development matter. ODM’s unilateral decision to partner with Jubilee, leaving out Wiper, Ford Kenya and ANC left coalition members in an awkward situation.  President Uhuru Kenyatta and Opposition leader Raila Odinga at the Muthaiga gold club Uhuru is expected to begin his Nyanza tour with Raila after the address. More on this: Nasa lawmakers divided on Uhuru’s Parliament address Also read:It was a painful handshake, Raila defends pact with Uhuru Click here for the latest political news